───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PREAMBLE
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This Contributive Heritage License ("CHL") v1.3 builds on the GNU Affero
General Public License Version 3 (AGPL-3.0) and adds a heritage revenue-
sharing mechanism so that every project and contributor in the Heritage Chain
above a commercializing fork receives a proportional share of Revenue generated
downstream.

The Heritage Chain is modelled as a tree. The Root Project — Vapour — owes
nothing to anyone. All payment flows UPWARD toward the root, not downward.
Every Monetizing Party pays a share to all Verified Contributors at every
level above them in the Heritage Chain, from their immediate upstream parent
all the way to the Root Project.

NOTE FOR VAPOUR: The sole contributor (KiwiOnGit) has filed an Opt-Out
Declaration and is not currently accepting revenue-sharing distributions or
imposing payment obligations on direct downstream forks with respect to their
share. See CHL-COMPLIANCE.json for full details. This may be revoked in writing
at any time.

Participation in revenue sharing is voluntary. Any Verified Contributor may
file an Opt-Out Declaration stating that they do not wish to receive revenue
shares, do not wish to impose revenue-sharing obligations on their downstream
forks, or both. An opted-out contributor is skipped in the payment chain
without affecting distributions owed to others.

Revenue-sharing acceptance operates on an individual basis. A contributor who
does not accept forfeits only their own share; that share redistributes pro
rata among Accepting Contributors. No single contributor can block distributions
owed to others.

This License closes the network-services loophole: deploying the Program or
any Derivative Work over a network — as SaaS, PaaS, API, or any hosted form —
triggers the same source-availability and revenue-sharing obligations as
physical distribution.

