0. DEFINITIONS

"This License" means CHL v1.3, incorporating AGPL-3.0 by reference plus the
provisions herein.

"The Program" means any copyrightable work licensed under this License.

"You" means each licensee.

"Root Project" means the original Program at the topmost level of the Heritage
Chain. The Root Project has no upstream payment obligations. For this project,
the Root Project is Vapour.

"Upstream Project" means any ancestor in the Heritage Chain above the current
work.

"Heritage Chain" means the Root Project and all identifiable Upstream Projects
forming a continuous lineage of derivation.

"Verified Contributor" means any individual or organization who has made
substantive contributions to the Root Project or any Upstream Project, as
evidenced by commit history, copyright notices, or explicit attribution.

"Substantial Improvement" means an addition to a Derivative Work that (a) adds
materially new functionality not present in any Upstream Project, (b) comprises
at least five percent (5%) of the codebase by meaningful lines of code, or (c)
is designated as a Substantial Improvement by written agreement of existing
Accepting Contributors in the Heritage Chain. Cosmetic changes, reformatting,
and dependency updates do not qualify.

"Registered Fork Contributor" means the author of a Derivative Work who has
(a) made a Substantial Improvement and (b) registered that improvement in the
public Heritage Chain Registry under Section 3.7. Registered Fork Contributors
are eligible to receive revenue shares from their own downstream Monetizing
Parties.

"Monetizing Party" means any licensee who generates Revenue from the Program
or a Derivative Work.

"Net Revenue" means gross receipts attributable to the Program or Derivative
Work, less: (a) documented third-party payment-processing fees actually paid;
(b) sales taxes, VAT, and equivalent taxes collected and remitted to government
authorities; (c) documented refunds and chargebacks. No other deductions are
permitted.

"Revenue" means Net Revenue as defined above.

"Attributable Revenue" means Revenue determined to be attributable to the
Program or Derivative Work under Section 3.5.

"Commercial Use" means any use resulting in Revenue, including Network Use.

"Derivative Work" means any modification, enhancement, fork, or derivative of
the Program.

"Network Use" means making the Program or Derivative Work available to third
parties over a computer network, including SaaS, PaaS, API, and hosted
deployments.

"Corresponding Source" means all source code needed to generate, install, and
run the Program or Derivative Work, including build scripts and server-side
application code used in Network Use.

"Accepting Contributor" means a Verified Contributor or Registered Fork
Contributor who has provided explicit written acceptance per Section 4.5 and
has not filed an Opt-Out Declaration under Section 4.6.

"Opt-Out Declaration" means a written notice filed under Section 4.6.

"De Minimis Threshold" means five hundred US dollars (USD $500) of Attributable
Revenue in a calendar quarter. Revenue-sharing obligations do not arise until
the Monetizing Party's Attributable Revenue exceeds this threshold.

"CHL Compliance File" means the single machine-readable CHL-COMPLIANCE.json
file described in Section 6.1 that consolidates all required metadata.


