12. TERMINATION — CURE BEFORE TERMINATION

12.1 Cure Period Replaces Automatic Termination

Rights under this License do NOT terminate automatically upon a violation. Upon
any breach:
  (a) The discovering party delivers written notice of the specific breach;
  (b) The breaching party has ninety (90) days from receipt of notice to cure;
  (c) If cured within ninety (90) days, no termination occurs;
  (d) If not cured, rights terminate automatically at the end of that period.

This cure-before-termination rule applies to all violations except willful
repeated violations where the same breach has been cured and re-committed within
a twelve (12) month period, in which case automatic termination applies upon the
second occurrence.

12.2 Effect of Termination

Upon termination: cease all distribution and Network Use; complete all pending
revenue-sharing distributions; retain records for seven (7) years.

12.3 Reinstatement

Rights may be reinstated by curing all outstanding violations and providing
written notice of cure to the party who issued the breach notice.


